            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/52954",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This is not a bug, but the intended behavior. Possibly documentation needs to be updated (and it will). \r\n\r\nIn ZF2, Zend\\Uri represents all kinds of URIs, and supports composing, parsing, validating and manipulating both absolute and relative URIs. For this reason, Uri::validate() is very basic and in fact almost always succeeds. \r\n\r\nIf you want to make sure a URI is both valid and absolute, use:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n$uri->isValid() && $uri->isAbsolute()\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
